# masterfabric_backend Conventions

- Domain -> Application -> Infrastructure (strict dependency rule; domain imports nothing external).
- Files: `snake_case.go`; packages: `lowercase` (single word).
- Interfaces: descriptive, no `I` prefix (`UserRepository`, not `IUserRepository`).
- Constructors: `NewXxx()` returning pointer.
- Use cases: `Execute(ctx, req) (resp, error)` pattern.
- Errors: `domainerr.New(code, message, cause)` from `internal/shared/errors`; wrap with `fmt.Errorf("...: %w", err)`.
- `response.Error` never sends `err.Error()` to the client (CWE-209); full detail goes to `slog`.
- Multi-tenancy: not used in MVP; structure kept for parity.
- After schema changes: run `goose -dir internal/infrastructure/postgres/migrations postgres "$DATABASE_DSN" up`.
